"content\":\"https://up-j-gemgem.ubiquityjournal.website/articles\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"6\",{\"property\":\"og:site_name\",\"content\":\"eGEMs (Generating Evidence \u0026 Methods to improve patient outcomes)\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"7\",{\"property\":\"og:locale\",\"content\":\"en\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"8\",{\"property\":\"og:image\",\"content\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-gemgem-public/journals/1/journalThumbnail_en_US.jpg\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"9\",{\"property\":\"og:image:width\",\"content\":\"600\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"10\",{\"property\":\"og:image:height\",\"content\":\"600\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"11\",{\"property\":\"og:image:alt\",\"content\":\"Thumbnail\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"12\",{\"property\":\"og:type\",\"content\":\"website\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"13\",{\"name\":\"twitter:card\",\"content\":\"summary\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"14\",{\"name\":\"twitter:title\",\"content\":\"Articles | eGEMs (Generating Evidence \u0026 Methods to improve patient outcomes)\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"15\",{\"name\":\"twitter:image\",\"content\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-gemgem-public/journals/1/journalThumbnail_en_US.jpg\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"16\",{\"name\":\"twitter:image:alt\",\"content\":\"Thumbnail\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"17\",{\"name\":\"twitter:image:width\",\"content\":\"600\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",\"18\",{\"name\":\"twitter:image:height\",\"content\":\"600\"}],[\"$\",\"link\",\"19\",{\"rel\":\"icon\",\"href\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-gemgem-public/journals/1/favicon_en_US.png\"}],[\"$\",\"$Lc2\",\"20\",{}]]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"c3:I[434075,[\"https://journal-assets.ubiquity.press/2.15.3/_next/static/chunks/0.042brxapcc9.js\",\"https://journal-assets.ubiquity.press/2.15.3/_next/static/chunks/04gqki4k-.2k..js\",\"https://journal-assets.ubiquity.press/2.15.3/_next/static/chunks/0~kmv70xqzcbe.js\",\"https://journal-assets.ubiquity.press/2.15.3/_next/static/chunks/0k9p3v0~wez6r.js\",\"https://journal-assets.ubiquity.press/2.15.3/_next/static/chunks/136skzvwn9brd.js\",\"https://journal-assets.ubiquity.press/2.15.3/_next/static/chunks/0izg206h8uh1d.js\",\"https://journal-assets.ubiquity.press/2.15.3/_next/static/chunks/05o9fpx1yg-yq.js\",\"https://journal-assets.ubiquity.press/2.15.3/_next/static/chunks/0sii9apoit0br.js\",\"https://journal-assets.ubiquity.press/2.15.3/_next/static/chunks/0p99645pr1ast.js\",\"https://journal-assets.ubiquity.press/2.15.3/_next/static/chunks/0zy_co6p1vn6h.js\",\"https://journal-assets.ubiquity.press/2.15.3/_next/static/chunks/0rsv3kejmnl5z.js\"],\"Client\"]\nc4:T1bb2,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv id=\"focusAndScope\"\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch2\u003eFocus and Scope\u003c/h2\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e is \u003ca href=\"http://www.academyhealth.org/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAcademyHealth\u003c/a\u003e’s peer-reviewed, open access journal created to accelerate research and quality improvement using electronic health data. Launched in 2013 by AcademyHealth's \u003ca href=\"http://www.academyhealth.org/EDMForumStory\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eElectronic Data Methods (EDM) Forum\u003c/a\u003e, \u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e has published more than 160 papers featuring cutting-edge work from leaders in the field and is a premier journal for approaches to redesigning the health system.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eFor more information about the inner workings of \u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e, please see the journal's official \u003ca href=\"https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/ubiquity-partner-network/up/journal/egems/egems-governance-policy.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eGovernance Policy\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv id=\"publicationFrequency\"\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch2\u003ePublication Frequency\u003c/h2\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe journal’s general issue publishes online as a continuous volume and issue throughout the year. Articles appear as soon as they are ready to ensure that there are no unnecessary delays in getting content publicly available.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv id=\"openAccessPolicy\"\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch2\u003eOpen Access Policy\u003c/h2\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis journal provides immediate open access to its content on the principle that making research freely available to the public supports a greater global exchange of knowledge.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAuthors of articles published remain the copyright holders and grant third parties the right to use, reproduce, and share the article according to the \u003ca href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eCreative Commons\u003c/a\u003e license agreement.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn order to be sustainable and maintain open access status, \u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e charges an APC per published paper. This fee covers the cost of managing rigorous peer review, thorough copyediting and layout design as well as publication and promotion.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAuthors are encouraged to publish their data in recommended repositories. For a list of generic and subject specific repositories that meet our peer review criteria, see \u003ca href=\"http://oad.simmons.edu/oadwiki/Data_repositories\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ehere\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv id=\"custom-0\"\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch2\u003eAnnotation\u003c/h2\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eThe journal platform includes in-browser annotation and text highlighting options on full text formats via \u003ca href=\"https://web.hypothes.is/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ehypothes.is\u003c/a\u003e. Readers will require a \u003ca href=\"https://web.hypothes.is/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ehypothes.is\u003c/a\u003e account to create annotations, and will have the option to make these publicly available, available to a group, or private.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv id=\"sponsors\"\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch2\u003eSponsors\u003c/h2\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e operates as a program unit within AcademyHealth, a 501c3 nonprofit organization and a leading national organization serving the fields of health services and policy research and the professionals who produce and use this important work. Together with its members, AcademyHealth offers programs and services that support the development and use of rigorous, relevant and timely evidence to increase the quality, accessibility, and value of health care, to reduce disparities, and to improve health. A trusted broker of information, AcademyHealth brings stakeholders together to address the current and future needs of an evolving health system, inform health policy, and translate evidence into action.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca href=\"http://www.academyhealth.org\"\u003eAcademyHealth\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv id=\"history\"\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch2\u003eJournal History\u003c/h2\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eeGEMs (Generating Evidence and Methods to improve patient outcomes)\u003c/em\u003e\u003cspan\u003e is AcademyHealth’s open access, peer-reviewed online journal dedicated to accelerating research and quality improvement using electronic health data. The journal first began publishing in 2013 as part of the mission of the \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://www.academyhealth.org/EDMForumStory\" target=\"_blank\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en-GB\u0026amp;q=http://www.academyhealth.org/EDMForumStory\u0026amp;source=gmail\u0026amp;ust=1493896840711000\u0026amp;usg=AFQjCNHoMaginov6nsWogaQubMkdOro1uQ\"\u003eEDM (Electronic Data Methods) Forum\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e, a community supported by the \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.ahrq.gov/\" target=\"_blank\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en-GB\u0026amp;q=https://www.ahrq.gov/\u0026amp;source=gmail\u0026amp;ust=1493896840711000\u0026amp;usg=AFQjCNGQesD_n36MlEjF4U5c3bRXWjOL-g\"\u003eAgency for Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ)\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e with the goal of advancing the national dialogue on the use of electronic health data for research and quality improvement. Since its launch, \u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e\u003cspan\u003e has published over 180 papers with well over 150,000 downloads—all highlighting cutting-edge work from leaders in the field and sharing emerging approaches to redesigning the health system. As \u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003eeGEMs’\u003c/em\u003e\u003cspan\u003e publication numbers grew, all journal articles were indexed in Google Scholar, the Directory of Open Access Journals, EBSCOhost, and the National Library of Medicine’s PubMed Central. With the close of the AHRQ grant in 2016, \u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e\u003cspan\u003e became AcademyHealth’s first in-house journal, and continues to publish methods, lessons, and research that contribute to the next generation of learning health systems.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv id=\"lockssLicense\"\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch2\u003eJournal Archiving\u003c/h2\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe journal’s publisher, Ubiquity Press, focuses on making content discoverable and accessible through indexing services. Content is also archived around the world to ensure long-term availability.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e is indexed in \u003ca href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=egems%5BJournal%5D\"\u003eNLM Pubmed Central\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"http://www.crossref.org/\"\u003eCrossRef\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"http://www.kbplus.ac.uk/kbplus/\"\u003eJISC KB+\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"http://www.sherpa.ac.uk\"\u003eSHERPA RoMEO\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"http://www.doaj.org/\"\u003eDirectory of Open Access Journals\u003c/a\u003e (DOAJ), \u003ca href=\"/jms/manager/setup/cengage.com\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eCengage Learning\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\"http://scholar.google.com/\"\u003eGoogle Scholar\u003c/a\u003e. In addition, all journals are available for harvesting via \u003ca href=\"http://www.openarchives.org/pmh/\"\u003eOAI-PMH\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eTo ensure permanency of all publications, this journal also utilises \u003ca href=\"http://www.clockss.org\"\u003eCLOCKSS\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\"http://www.lockss.org/\"\u003eLOCKSS\u003c/a\u003e archiving systems to create permanent archives for the purposes of preservation and restoration.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf \u003cem\u003e\u003c/em\u003ethe journal is not indexed by your preferred service, please let us know by emailing \u003ca href=\"mailto:support@ubiquitypress.com\"\u003esupport@ubiquitypress.com\u003c/a\u003e or alternatively by making an indexing request directly with the service.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c!-- CLOCKSS system has permission to ingest, preserve, and serve this Archival Unit --\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"c5:T132d,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e operates a two-stage, double-blind peer review process. Authors and reviewers are anonymous to each other at all stages of the review. After accepting the invitation to complete the review of this article, please refer to the information set out below to assist you in your feedback. The peer review form is available above (section 5). You can also upload additional files containing further comments relevant to the review on this page:\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch3\u003eGeneral guide to aid the review:\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e1) General comments and summary of recommendation\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eDoes the article fit within the scope of the journal?\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e2) Content\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cbr /\u003ePlease consider the originality, relevance and rigour of the submission and the author’s depth of understanding of the issues being researched. Please comment on the adequacy of the author’s referencing and whether or not the existing knowledge base has been explored and built upon. Please comment on methodologies used and their appropriateness, and the author’s use of the evidential base. Does the conclusion reflect the argument in the main body text and bring something new to the debate?\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e3) Structure and argument\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cbr /\u003ePlease consider whether the abstract summarises the arguments in a succinct and accurate way. Is the manuscript logically structured and do the arguments flow coherently? Is there enough reference to methodology in the introduction and are the arguments fully evidenced and substantiated ? Does the introduction signpost the arguments in the logical way and does the conclusion adequately summarise them?\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e4) Figures/tables\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cbr /\u003ePlease comment on the author’s use of tables, charts, figures or maps – their relevance in terms of illustrating the arguments and supporting the evidential base, the quality of the formatting and presentation.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e5) Formatting\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cbr /\u003eDoes the submitted file adhere to the general author guidelines listed for the journal? Are the citations and references formatted to house-style?\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e6) Language\u003cbr /\u003e\u003c/strong\u003eIs the text well written and jargon free? Please comment on the quality of English and need for grammatical improvement\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eProvide comments and suggestions for improvement, if required, with additional references or possible clarification of arguments, etc. You can also add comments to the text of the article and upload your comments, if you see fit.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch3\u003eAdditional guidance\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e' senior editors have developed the following guidance for reviewers in evaluating the usefulness and quality of submissions for publication in \u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eDo the authors lead by explaining \u003cem\u003ewhy?\u003c/em\u003e \u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eSubmissions should discuss the motivation for developing a particular innovation or approach that addresses shared challenges.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eSubmissions should convey as specifically as possible how the work is important beyond the context of traditional research, and how the work has the potential to advance knowledge and practice. For example, how will the innovation or approach contribute to building a learning health system that can improve care and outcomes?\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eDo the authors clearly articulate how they hope other researchers and stakeholders will benefit from the manuscript?\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eSubmissions should focus on generalizable lessons learned, success, and failure.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eWhat is the evidence that the proposed approach works as promised?\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eIf, for example, a new method is proposed:\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eto control for selection bias in EHR-based CER, have the authors presented evidence that bias is reduced or eliminated?\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003efor validation studies to identify patients with a particular condition, have the authors reported sensitivity and specificity of the method?\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eIf there are there certain situations in which the approach is likely to work better or worse, these should be explained.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eAre limitations of the highlighted innovation or approach discussed?\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eSubmissions should explain how limitations may affect the generalizability of findings and future research.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eWhen applicable, submissions should discuss how the innovation or approach could be evaluated further in the current setting or in other environments.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eIf the submission proposes new methods or reflections on null results, next steps or lessons learned should be proposed to guide future efforts. \u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eDo the authors invite dialogue and participation in developing new approaches? \u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eWhen applicable, submissions should provide suggestions for specific ways in which the community may generate solutions and ongoing dialogue. \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eThese include descriptions of possible next steps, strategies for dissemination, and openness to comments from readers.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"bb:[\"$\",\"$Lc3\",null,{\"journal\":{\"title\":\"eGEMs (Generating Evidence \u0026 Methods to improve patient outcomes)\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"initials\":\"eGEMs\",\"abbreviation\":\"eGEMs\",\"description\":\"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThis title is no longer publishing and submissions have been closed. \u003cem\u003eeGEMs \u003c/em\u003ehas transitioned from a free-standing journal to a special section within the journal \u003ca href=\\\"https://www.journals.elsevier.com/healthcare-the-journal-of-delivery-science-and-innovation/editorial-board\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"\u003eHealthcare: The Journal of Delivery Science and Innovation\u003c/a\u003e. All published papers are currently still freely available on this website, but any new submissions should be sent to \u003cem\u003eHealthcare\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eeGEMs (Generating Evidence \u0026amp; Methods to improve patient outcomes)\u003c/em\u003e was \u003ca href=\\\"http://academyhealth.org/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"\u003eAcademyHealth\u003c/a\u003e’s open access, peer-reviewed online journal dedicated to accelerating research and quality improvement using electronic health data. \u003ca href=\\\"/about\\\"\u003eRead more\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\",\"focus_scope\":\"$c4\",\"editorial_policies\":\"\",\"review_guidelines\":\"$c5\",\"archiving\":\"\",\"eissn\":\"2327-9214\",\"print_issn\":\"\",\"terms_conditions\":\"\",\"privacy_policy\":\"\u003cp\u003eThe names and email addresses entered in this journal site will be used exclusively for the stated purposes of this journal and will not be made available for any other purpose or to any other party. For more information, see the full Privacy Policy \u003ca href=\\\"/about/privacy-policy/\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\"\u003ehere\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"published_by\":\"Ubiquity Press\",\"publisher_url\":\"http://www.ubiquitypress.com\",\"supported_submission_locales\":\"[\\\"en\\\"]\",\"cover\":{\"link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-gemgem-public/journals/1/journalCoverImage_en_US.jpg\",\"alt_text\":\"Cover Image\"},\"submission_disabled\":false,\"jpps_badge_enabled\":false,\"remove_journal_terminology\":false,\"accessibility_statement_link\":\"https://journals.support.ubiquity.pub/category/190-accessibility-statements\",\"jpps_path\":\"\",\"jol\":\"\",\"thumbnail\":{\"link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-gemgem-public/journals/1/journalThumbnail_en_US.jpg\",\"alt_text\":\"Thumbnail\"},\"favicon\":{\"link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-gemgem-public/journals/1/favicon_en_US.png\",\"alt_text\":\"]u[ favicon\"},\"colors\":{\"primary\":\"#29549F\",\"secondary\":\"#9D6D0B\"},\"google_analytics\":null,\"has_dois\":true,\"language\":{\"default_lang\":\"en\",\"supported\":[\"en\"],\"supported_submission_languages\":[\"en\"],\"locale_tag_style\":\"compact\"},\"sections\":[{\"name\":\"Case study\",\"id\":2,\"order\":1,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Commentary / Editorial\",\"id\":5,\"order\":2,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Comparative case study\",\"id\":3,\"order\":3,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Empirical research\",\"id\":7,\"order\":4,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Model / Framework\",\"id\":6,\"order\":5,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Protocol\",\"id\":8,\"order\":6,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}},{\"name\":\"Review\",\"id\":4,\"order\":7,\"policy\":{\"open_submissions\":true,\"indexed\":true,\"peer_reviewed\":true,\"only_editors\":false,\"text\":\"\",\"display\":false}}],\"licenses\":{\"name\":\"\",\"code\":\"\",\"link\":\"\"},\"subject_taxonomy\":[],\"ojs_version\":\"3.4.0.10\",\"static_pages\":[]},\"collections\":[{\"description\":\"\u003cp\u003eThis special collection, sponsored by the \u003ca href=\\\"https://www.ahrq.gov/\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\"\u003eAgency for Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ)\u003c/a\u003e, highlights new data insights and capabilities that respond to rapid change in the way researchers, clinicians, patients, policymakers and others use data to transform health care. The articles below showcase research that leverages data as a driver of health system transformation and include traditional general hypothesis testing, predictive analytics research, and case studies that showcase frontline innovations within health systems.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"short_description\":\"\u003cp\u003eThis special collection, sponsored by the \u003ca href=\\\"https://www.ahrq.gov/\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\"\u003eAgency for Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ)\u003c/a\u003e, highlights new data insights and capabilities that respond to rapid change in the way researchers, clinicians, patients, policymakers and others use data to transform health care.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"Data’s Potential to Drive Health System Transformation\",\"creation_date\":\"2019-08-02T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-gemgem-public/journals/1/categories/5-category.jpg\",\"id\":5,\"editors\":[],\"path\":\"data-s-potential-to-drive-health-system-transformation\",\"user_sorting\":0},{\"description\":\"\u003cp\u003e\u003cb\u003eHealth Care Transformation through Delivery System Research\\r \u003c/b\u003e\\r \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\\r \\r The articles below are part of a special collection commemorating 25 years of the \u003ca href=\\\"http://www.hcsrn.org/en/\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\"\u003eHealth Care System Research Network’s\u003c/a\u003e (HCSRN's) rigorous research to improve health outcomes and health systems’ performance by leveraging electronic health data. This new collection highlights, among other things, advances in personalized cancer care, the optimal use of AI in health care, and the evolution of common data models, featuring work from Kaiser Permanente, Intermountain Healthcare and others.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"short_description\":\"This collection commemorates 25 years of the \u003ca href=\\\"http://www.hcsrn.org/en/\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\"\u003eHealth Care System Research Network’s\u003c/a\u003e (HCSRN's) rigorous research to improve health outcomes and health systems’ performance by leveraging electronic health data. These articles highlight advances in personalized cancer care, the optimal use of AI in health care, and the evolution of common data models. \u003c/p\u003e\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"HCSRN Special Collection\",\"creation_date\":\"2019-03-25T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-gemgem-public/journals/1/categories/4-category.jpg\",\"id\":4,\"editors\":[],\"path\":\"hcsrn-special-collection\",\"user_sorting\":1},{\"description\":\"\u003cp\u003eArticles in this collection are the result of a call for papers aligned with the themes of AcademyHealth’s \u003ca href=\\\"https://www.academyhealth.org/events/2017-04/2017-health-datapalooza\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\"\u003eHealth Datapalooza\u003c/a\u003e 2017, a one-of-a-kind conference bringing together a diverse audience of more than 1,200 people, all working to harness data and technology to improve health. Health Datapalooza is the \u003ca href=\\\"http://www.healthdatapalooza.org/\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\"\u003eannual gathering place\u003c/a\u003e for the people and organizations creating knowledge from data and pioneering innovations that drive health policy and practice.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"short_description\":\"\u003cp\u003eArticles in this collection are the result of a call for papers aligned with the themes of AcademyHealth’s \u003ca href=\\\"https://www.academyhealth.org/events/2017-04/2017-health-datapalooza\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\"\u003eHealth Datapalooza\u003c/a\u003e 2017, a one-of-a-kind conference bringing together a diverse audience of more than 1,200 people, all working to harness data and technology to improve health. \u003c/p\u003e\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"Health Datapalooza 2017\",\"creation_date\":\"2018-11-21T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-gemgem-public/journals/1/categories/3-category.jpg\",\"id\":3,\"editors\":[],\"path\":\"health-datapalooza-2017\",\"user_sorting\":2},{\"description\":\"\u003cp\u003e“Better Decisions Together” is a special collection in \u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e—produced in partnership with AHRQ's \u003ca href=\\\"https://pccds-ln.org/\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\"\u003e Patient-Centered Clinical Decision Support Learning Network\u003c/a\u003e—highlighting methods and strategies to advance the science of patient-centered clinical decision support.\\r \u003c/p\u003e\\r \u003cp\u003ePapers in this collection show how complex patient data such as lab results and genomic data can be delivered to patients in ways that they can understand and use. Each one emphasizes the potential of patient-centered clinical decision support to address broad issues in the U.S. health care system regarding quality and safety while also achieving better outcomes and better patient and provider satisfaction.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"short_description\":\"\u003cp\u003e“Better Decisions Together” is a special collection in \u003cem\u003eeGEMs\u003c/em\u003e—produced in partnership with AHRQ's \u003ca href=\\\"https://pccds-ln.org/\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\"\u003e Patient-Centered Clinical Decision Support Learning Network\u003c/a\u003e—highlighting methods and strategies to advance the science of patient-centered clinical decision support.\\r \u003c/p\u003e\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"Better Decisions Together\",\"creation_date\":\"2018-06-05T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-gemgem-public/journals/1/categories/1-category.png\",\"id\":1,\"editors\":[],\"path\":\"better-decisions-together\",\"user_sorting\":3},{\"description\":\"Reflecting the work of members of the HVHC, a number of the papers highlight insights from a two-year multi-site project on improving sepsis care with practical recommendations on strategies to align and clean data from multiple institutions in order to conduct meaningful analytics. Other papers focus on data-driven strategies for detecting issues such as risk of low health literacy, severity of illness and cost based on ICU length of stay, and hospitals’ use of observation stays to avoid penalties for hospital readmissions. Sponsored by Intermountain Healthcare, the special issue also points to high-level infrastructure issues with papers on leveraging diverse data sources to describe delivery systems and electronic medical record systems that produce computable data.\",\"short_description\":\"Highlighting lessons learned from High Value Healthcare Collaborative , a provider learning network committed to improving health care value through data and collaboration\",\"ordering\":\"datePublished-2\",\"name\":\"High Value Healthcare Collaborative Special Issue\",\"creation_date\":\"2017-12-15T00:00:00+00:00\",\"show\":true,\"cover_alt\":null,\"cover_link\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/jnl-up-j-gemgem-public/journals/1/categories/2-category.png\",\"id\":2,\"editors\":[],\"path\":\"high-value-healthcare-collaborative-special-issue\",\"user_sorting\":4}],\"total\":295,\"query\":{\"page\":1,\"items\":25,\"collection\":\"$undefined\",\"taxonomy\":\"$undefined\",\"section\":\"$undefined\"}}]\n"])</script></body></html>